## When to use
When you need to inspect and understand detailed information about your system's CPU usage across multiple processors or cores.

## Approach
Use the `shell_exec` tool with the `mpstat` command. Common advanced options include `-P ALL` for monitoring all CPUs, `-I` for displaying interrupt statistics per CPU, and `-l 10` to specify an interval of 1 second with a delay between each sample (in this case, 10 samples will be collected). For continuous monitoring, you can use `mpstat -P ALL`.

## Example
```sh
shell_exec "mpstat -P ALL"
```
This example uses the `shell_exec` tool to run an `mpstat` command that monitors CPU usage across all available processors or cores.

## Pitfalls
- Ensure that the system has installed and configured the necessary utilities for running shell commands.
- Be aware of the interval duration when using continuous monitoring as it can generate a large amount of output quickly.